description:
This is a 11 minute workout called 'Core Strength' from the channel Peter Donohoe.
The workout falls under Strength/Body weight.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Rhythmic Powerhouse and The Disciplined Grind vibe.
The The Rhythmic Powerhouse vibe means Beat-driven, strong but fluid, music-infused. This is especially good for When you want strength and rhythm to blend seamlessly. The The Disciplined Grind vibe means No excuses, no distractions, just execute. This is especially good for When you want pure focus and efficiency..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Build a solid foundation between your upper and lower body with Pete and Laine by isolating your core during this fast-paced strength workout....
